<taxonomicName id="D2712F2F73DEB12A648685EAB9AC701C" LSID="45293323-B7B5-512F-A945-8C6968C9C60D" authority="Hering" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Platensina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platensina tetrica" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetrica">Platensina tetrica Hering</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2734428FC78BFF12239EC8FD7AA10470" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="37732EB964B578B970644761AC587540" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="B62E1DF3043A42D346B2DE7F7094F715" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Platensina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platensina tetrica" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetrica">Platensina tetrica</taxonomicName>
Hering, 1939a: 179. Type locality Trichinopolis, Tamil Nadu, India.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="033839058C6AE69D85726D33FA6205FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="DE5D4641FB0E87E33F921FF91ACE259F" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Platensina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platensina fukienica" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fukienica">Platensina fukienica</taxonomicName>
Hering, 1939b: 146. Type locality Fujian, China.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D509EB87CE33638A0B671E850342B5F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="5B84F3514A63359D29205C6990AFA6F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="19DD9BDE202EF60A65341147EC48D468" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species was adequately described by 
<bibRefCitation id="63AD844F289C0487C02802D932D2CE02" author="Hering, EM" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen Siebenter Internationale Kongress fuer Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="165 - 190" refId="B16" refString="Hering, EM, 1939a. Neue Trypetidae der Erde. Verhandlungen Siebenter Internationale Kongress fuer Entomologie 1 (7): 165 - 190" title="Neue Trypetidae der Erde." volume="1" year="1939 a">Hering (1939a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C02802CC9C914662347B85558484264D" author="Hering, EM" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen Siebenter Internationale Kongress fuer Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B17" refString="Hering, EM, 1939b. Vier neue Bohrfliegen von Fukien (Dipt. Trypet.). Decheniana 98(B): 143-147." title="Vier neue Bohrfliegen von Fukien (Dipt. Trypet.). Decheniana 98 (B): 143 - 147." year="1939 b">b</bibRefCitation>
) and is characterised by the reduced and often indistinct hyaline markings. Indian specimens were not available for study but wings of both 
<taxonomicName id="2644F0641B21058E9D67C23FE6F38898" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. tetrica" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetrica">
<emphasis id="F50A6666A9685BD2F0841DB889BD09C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. tetrica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hering and 
<taxonomicName id="A7BE823CB47CC0464AA7276B48FA5446" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. fukienica" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fukienica">
<emphasis id="C2F079FA7963A891C491DE05DF5917EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. fukienica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hering, considered synonyms by 
<bibRefCitation id="D4001DA590ED0BDCB4921FAB9197C2FD" author="Hancock, DL" journalOrPublisher="Australian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="305 - 320" refId="B9" refString="Hancock, DL, 2012. Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya. Australian Entomologist 39 (4): 305 - 320" title="Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya." volume="39" year="2012">Hancock (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, were illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="F19274BFA7B43394D15FDFF33B065A39" author="Wang, XJ" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Proceedings of the Linnean Society London Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B27" refString="Wang, XJ, 1998. The Fruit Flies (Diptera: Tephritidae) of the East Asian Region. Dong Wu Fen Lei Xue Bao (Supplement 21): 1-338." title="The Fruit Flies (Diptera: Tephritidae) of the East Asian Region. Dong Wu Fen Lei Xue Bao (Supplement 21): 1 - 338." year="1998">Wang (1998)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="20E033584AB9F582CE5E7D148716D126" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EF4A0513043780518CDE126EFB75786F" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="30F36AFB2C2E1C5A7C0EAE40411CE24F" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species is known in India only from the type locality in Tamil Nadu. Elsewhere, it is known from China, Taiwan, Vietnam and West Malaysia (
<bibRefCitation id="434B6163B2A491D1F734F1E38A0F6204" author="Hancock, DL" journalOrPublisher="Australian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="305 - 320" refId="B9" refString="Hancock, DL, 2012. Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya. Australian Entomologist 39 (4): 305 - 320" title="Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya." volume="39" year="2012">Hancock 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
